5. Energetic efficiency: Overall conversion of glucose oxidation energy to ATP achieves approximately 52% efficiency—remarkable compared to human-engineered systems.
6. Entropy production: The entropy production rate $\phi = \sum v_j A_j / T$ quantifies dissipation. Metabolic switches balance efficiency against speed.
7. Information costs: Biological information processing approaches but rarely reaches the Landauer limit, paying an "information tax" for accuracy and reliability in a noisy environment.

This "engine room" of the cell converts chemical potential into work, powering all the processes described in previous parts—from protein folding (Part II) to DNA replication (Part III). The thermodynamic principles established here will be essential for understanding multicellular organization (Part V) and neural computation (Part VII).

